 114     """The default method of calling the wrapper subprocess."""

 122         env=env,
 123         block=True,
 124         combine_stderr=True,
 125         return_object=False,
 126         write_to_stdout=False,
 127         nospin=True,

 164 def parse_special_directives(setup_entry, package_dir=None):
 165     # type: (S, Optional[STRING_TYPE]) -> S
 166     rv = setup_entry
 167     if not package_dir:
 168         package_dir = os.getcwd()
 169     if setup_entry.startswith("file:"):
 170         _, path = setup_entry.split("file:")
 171         path = path.strip()
 172         if os.path.exists(path):
 173             rv = read_source(path)
 174     elif setup_entry.startswith("attr:"):
 175         _, resource = setup_entry.split("attr:")
 176         resource = resource.strip()
 177         with temp_path():
 178             sys.path.insert(0, package_dir)
 179             if "." in resource:
 180                 resource, _, attribute = resource.rpartition(".")
 181             package, _, path = resource.partition(".")
 182             base_path = os.path.join(package_dir, package)
 183             if path:
 184                 path = os.path.join(base_path, os.path.join(*path.split(".")))
 185             else:
 186                 path = base_path
 187             if not os.path.exists(path) and os.path.exists("{0}.py".format(path)):
 188                 path = "{0}.py".format(path)
 189             elif os.path.isdir(path):
 190                 path = os.path.join(path, "__init__.py")
 191             rv = ast_parse_attribute_from_file(path, attribute)
 192             if rv:
 193                 return str(rv)
 194             module = importlib.import_module(resource)
 195             rv = getattr(module, attribute)
 196             if not isinstance(rv, six.string_types):
 197                 rv = str(rv)
 198     return rv

 201 def make_base_requirements(reqs):
 202     # type: (Sequence[STRING_TYPE]) -> Set[BaseRequirement]
 203     requirements = set()
 204     if not isinstance(reqs, (list, tuple, set)):
 205         reqs = [reqs]
 206     for req in reqs:
 207         if isinstance(req, BaseRequirement):
 208             requirements.add(req)
 209         elif pkg_resources_requirements is not None and isinstance(
 210             req, pkg_resources_requirements.Requirement
 211         ):
 212             requirements.add(BaseRequirement.from_req(req))
 213         elif req and isinstance(req, six.string_types) and not req.startswith("#"):
 214             requirements.add(BaseRequirement.from_string(req))
 215     return requirements

 218 def setuptools_parse_setup_cfg(path):
 219     from setuptools.config import read_configuration
 220 
 221     parsed = read_configuration(path)
 222     results = parsed.get("metadata", {})
 223     results.update(parsed.get("options", {}))
 224     results["install_requires"] = make_base_requirements(
 225         results.get("install_requires", [])
 226     )
 227     extras = {}
 228     for extras_section, extras_reqs in results.get("extras_require", {}).items():
 229         new_reqs = tuple(make_base_requirements(extras_reqs))
 230         if new_reqs:
 231             extras[extras_section] = new_reqs
 232     results["extras_require"] = extras
 233     results["setup_requires"] = make_base_requirements(results.get("setup_requires", []))
 234     return results

 237 def get_package_dir_from_setupcfg(parser, base_dir=None):
 238     # type: (configparser.ConfigParser, STRING_TYPE) -> Text
 239     if base_dir is not None:
 240         package_dir = base_dir
 241     else:
 242         package_dir = os.getcwd()
 243     if parser.has_option("options.packages.find", "where"):
 244         pkg_dir = parser.get("options.packages.find", "where")
 245         if isinstance(pkg_dir, Mapping):
 246             pkg_dir = pkg_dir.get("where")
 247         package_dir = os.path.join(package_dir, pkg_dir)
 248     elif parser.has_option("options", "packages"):
 249         pkg_dir = parser.get("options", "packages")
 250         if "find:" in pkg_dir:
 251             _, pkg_dir = pkg_dir.split("find:")
 252             pkg_dir = pkg_dir.strip()
 253             package_dir = os.path.join(package_dir, pkg_dir)
 254     elif os.path.exists(os.path.join(package_dir, "setup.py")):
 255         setup_py = ast_parse_setup_py(os.path.join(package_dir, "setup.py"))
 256         if "package_dir" in setup_py:
 257             package_lookup = setup_py["package_dir"]
 258             if not isinstance(package_lookup, Mapping):
 259                 package_dir = package_lookup
 260             package_dir = package_lookup.get(
 261                 next(iter(list(package_lookup.keys()))), package_dir
 262             )
 263     if not os.path.isabs(package_dir):
 264         if not base_dir:
 265             package_dir = os.path.join(os.path.getcwd(), package_dir)
 266         else:
 267             package_dir = os.path.join(base_dir, package_dir)
 268     return package_dir

 271 def get_name_and_version_from_setupcfg(parser, package_dir):
 272     # type: (configparser.ConfigParser, STRING_TYPE) -> Tuple[Optional[S], Optional[S]]
 273     name, version = None, None
 274     if parser.has_option("metadata", "name"):
 275         name = parse_special_directives(parser.get("metadata", "name"), package_dir)
 276     if parser.has_option("metadata", "version"):
 277         version = parse_special_directives(parser.get("metadata", "version"), package_dir)
 278     return name, version

 281 def get_extras_from_setupcfg(parser):
 282     # type: (configparser.ConfigParser) -> Dict[STRING_TYPE, Tuple[BaseRequirement, ...]]
 283     extras = {}  # type: Dict[STRING_TYPE, Tuple[BaseRequirement, ...]]
 284     if "options.extras_require" not in parser.sections():
 285         return extras
 286     extras_require_section = parser.options("options.extras_require")
 287     for section in extras_require_section:
 288         if section in ["options", "metadata"]:
 289             continue
 290         section_contents = parser.get("options.extras_require", section)
 291         section_list = section_contents.split("\n")
 292         section_extras = tuple(make_base_requirements(section_list))
 293         if section_extras:
 294             extras[section] = section_extras
 295     return extras

 298 def parse_setup_cfg(
 299     setup_cfg_contents,  # type: S
 300     base_dir,  # type: S
 301 ):
 302     # type: (...) -> Dict[S, Union[S, None, Set[BaseRequirement], List[S], Dict[STRING_TYPE, Tuple[BaseRequirement]]]]
 303     default_opts = {
 304         "metadata": {"name": "", "version": ""},
 305         "options": {
 306             "install_requires": "",
 307             "python_requires": "",
 308             "build_requires": "",
 309             "setup_requires": "",
 310             "extras": "",
 311             "packages.find": {"where": "."},
 312         },
 313     }
 314     parser = configparser.ConfigParser(default_opts)
 315     if six.PY2:
 316         buff = io.BytesIO(setup_cfg_contents)
 317         parser.readfp(buff)
 318     else:
 319         parser.read_string(setup_cfg_contents)
 320     results = {}
 321     package_dir = get_package_dir_from_setupcfg(parser, base_dir=base_dir)
 322     name, version = get_name_and_version_from_setupcfg(parser, package_dir)
 323     results["name"] = name
 324     results["version"] = version
 325     install_requires = set()  # type: Set[BaseRequirement]
 326     if parser.has_option("options", "install_requires"):
 327         install_requires = make_base_requirements(
 328             parser.get("options", "install_requires").split("\n")
 329         )
 330     results["install_requires"] = install_requires
 331     if parser.has_option("options", "python_requires"):
 332         results["python_requires"] = parse_special_directives(
 333             parser.get("options", "python_requires"), package_dir
 334         )
 335     if parser.has_option("options", "build_requires"):
 336         results["build_requires"] = parser.get("options", "build_requires")
 337     results["extras_require"] = get_extras_from_setupcfg(parser)
 338     return results

 341 @contextlib.contextmanager
 342 def _suppress_distutils_logs():
 343     # type: () -> Generator[None, None, None]
 344     """Hack to hide noise generated by `setup.py develop`.
 345 
 346     There isn't a good way to suppress them now, so let's monky-patch.
 347     See https://bugs.python.org/issue25392.
 348     """
 349 
 350     f = distutils.log.Log._log
 351 
 352     def _log(log, level, msg, args):
 353         if level >= distutils.log.ERROR:
 354             f(log, level, msg, args)
 355 
 356     distutils.log.Log._log = _log
 357     yield
 358     distutils.log.Log._log = f

 361 def build_pep517(source_dir, build_dir, config_settings=None, dist_type="wheel"):
 362     if config_settings is None:
 363         config_settings = {}
 364     requires, backend = get_pyproject(source_dir)
 365     hookcaller = HookCaller(source_dir, backend)
 366     if dist_type == "sdist":
 367         get_requires_fn = hookcaller.get_requires_for_build_sdist
 368         build_fn = hookcaller.build_sdist
 369     else:
 370         get_requires_fn = hookcaller.get_requires_for_build_wheel
 371         build_fn = hookcaller.build_wheel
 372 
 373     with BuildEnv() as env:
 374         env.pip_install(requires)
 375         reqs = get_requires_fn(config_settings)
 376         env.pip_install(reqs)
 377         return build_fn(build_dir, config_settings)

 380 @ensure_mkdir_p(mode=0o775)
 381 def _get_src_dir(root):
 382     # type: (AnyStr) -> AnyStr
 383     src = os.environ.get("PIP_SRC")
 384     if src:
 385         return src
 386     virtual_env = os.environ.get("VIRTUAL_ENV")
 387     if virtual_env is not None:
 388         return os.path.join(virtual_env, "src")
 389     if root is not None:
 390         # Intentionally don't match pip's behavior here -- this is a temporary copy
 391         src_dir = create_tracked_tempdir(prefix="requirementslib-", suffix="-src")
 392     else:
 393         src_dir = os.path.join(root, "src")
 394     return src_dir

 397 @lru_cache()
 398 def ensure_reqs(reqs):
 399     # type: (List[Union[S, PkgResourcesRequirement]]) -> List[PkgResourcesRequirement]
 400     import pkg_resources
 401 
 402     if not isinstance(reqs, Iterable):
 403         raise TypeError("Expecting an Iterable, got %r" % reqs)
 404     new_reqs = []
 405     for req in reqs:
 406         if not req:
 407             continue
 408         if isinstance(req, six.string_types):
 409             req = pkg_resources.Requirement.parse("{0}".format(str(req)))
 410         # req = strip_extras_markers_from_requirement(req)
 411         new_reqs.append(req)
 412     return new_reqs

 415 def _prepare_wheel_building_kwargs(
 416     ireq=None,  # type: Optional[InstallRequirement]
 417     src_root=None,  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 418     src_dir=None,  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 419     editable=False,  # type: bool

 448 class ScandirCloser(object):
 449     def __init__(self, path):
 450         self.iterator = scandir(path)
 451 
 452     def __next__(self):
 453         return next(iter(self.iterator))
 454 
 455     def __iter__(self):
 456         return self
 457 
 458     def next(self):
 459         return self.__next__()
 460 
 461     def close(self):
 462         if getattr(self.iterator, "close", None):
 463             self.iterator.close()
 464         else:
 465             pass

 468 def iter_metadata(path, pkg_name=None, metadata_type="egg-info"):
 469     # type: (AnyStr, Optional[AnyStr], AnyStr) -> Generator
 470     if pkg_name is not None:
 471         pkg_variants = get_name_variants(pkg_name)
 472     dirs_to_search = [path]
 473     while dirs_to_search:
 474         p = dirs_to_search.pop(0)
 475         with contextlib.closing(ScandirCloser(p)) as path_iterator:
 476             for entry in path_iterator:
 477                 if entry.is_dir():
 478                     entry_name, ext = os.path.splitext(entry.name)
 479                     if ext.endswith(metadata_type):
 480                         if pkg_name is None or entry_name.lower() in pkg_variants:
 481                             yield entry
 482                     elif not entry.name.endswith(metadata_type):
 483                         dirs_to_search.append(entry.path)

 486 def find_egginfo(target, pkg_name=None):
 487     # type: (AnyStr, Optional[AnyStr]) -> Generator
 488     egg_dirs = (
 489         egg_dir
 490         for egg_dir in iter_metadata(target, pkg_name=pkg_name)
 491         if egg_dir is not None
 492     )
 493     if pkg_name:
 494         yield next(iter(eggdir for eggdir in egg_dirs if eggdir is not None), None)
 495     else:
 496         for egg_dir in egg_dirs:
 497             yield egg_dir

 516 def get_distinfo_dist(path, pkg_name=None):
 517     # type: (S, Optional[S]) -> Optional[DistInfoDistribution]
 518     import pkg_resources
 519 
 520     dist_dir = next(iter(find_distinfo(path, pkg_name=pkg_name)), None)
 521     if dist_dir is not None:
 522         metadata_dir = dist_dir.path
 523         base_dir = os.path.dirname(metadata_dir)
 524         dist = next(iter(pkg_resources.find_distributions(base_dir)), None)
 525         if dist is not None:
 526             return dist
 527     return None

 530 def get_egginfo_dist(path, pkg_name=None):
 531     # type: (S, Optional[S]) -> Optional[EggInfoDistribution]
 532     import pkg_resources
 533 
 534     egg_dir = next(iter(find_egginfo(path, pkg_name=pkg_name)), None)
 535     if egg_dir is not None:
 536         metadata_dir = egg_dir.path
 537         base_dir = os.path.dirname(metadata_dir)
 538         path_metadata = pkg_resources.PathMetadata(base_dir, metadata_dir)
 539         dist_iter = pkg_resources.distributions_from_metadata(path_metadata.egg_info)
 540         dist = next(iter(dist_iter), None)
 541         if dist is not None:
 542             return dist
 543     return None

 546 def get_metadata(path, pkg_name=None, metadata_type=None):
 547     # type: (S, Optional[S], Optional[S]) -> Dict[S, Union[S, List[RequirementType], Dict[S, RequirementType]]]
 548     wheel_allowed = metadata_type == "wheel" or metadata_type is None
 549     egg_allowed = metadata_type == "egg" or metadata_type is None
 550     dist = None  # type: Optional[Union[DistInfoDistribution, EggInfoDistribution]]
 551     if wheel_allowed:
 552         dist = get_distinfo_dist(path, pkg_name=pkg_name)
 553     if egg_allowed and dist is None:
 554         dist = get_egginfo_dist(path, pkg_name=pkg_name)
 555     if dist is not None:
 556         return get_metadata_from_dist(dist)
 557     return {}

 560 @lru_cache()
 561 def get_extra_name_from_marker(marker):
 562     # type: (MarkerType) -> Optional[S]
 563     if not marker:
 564         raise ValueError("Invalid value for marker: {0!r}".format(marker))
 565     if not getattr(marker, "_markers", None):
 566         raise TypeError("Expecting a marker instance, received {0!r}".format(marker))
 567     for elem in marker._markers:
 568         if isinstance(elem, tuple) and elem[0].value == "extra":
 569             return elem[2].value
 570     return None

 573 def get_metadata_from_wheel(wheel_path):
 574     # type: (S) -> Dict[Any, Any]
 575     if not isinstance(wheel_path, six.string_types):
 576         raise TypeError("Expected string instance, received {0!r}".format(wheel_path))
 577     try:
 578         dist = Wheel(wheel_path)
 579     except Exception:
 580         pass
 581     metadata = dist.metadata
 582     name = metadata.name
 583     version = metadata.version
 584     requires = []
 585     extras_keys = getattr(metadata, "extras", [])  # type: List[STRING_TYPE]
 586     extras = {
 587         k: [] for k in extras_keys
 588     }  # type: Dict[STRING_TYPE, List[RequirementType]]
 589     for req in getattr(metadata, "run_requires", []):
 590         parsed_req = init_requirement(req)
 591         parsed_marker = parsed_req.marker
 592         if parsed_marker:
 593             extra = get_extra_name_from_marker(parsed_marker)
 594             if extra is None:
 595                 requires.append(parsed_req)
 596                 continue
 597             if extra not in extras:
 598                 extras[extra] = []
 599             parsed_req = strip_extras_markers_from_requirement(parsed_req)
 600             extras[extra].append(parsed_req)
 601         else:
 602             requires.append(parsed_req)
 603     return {"name": name, "version": version, "requires": requires, "extras": extras}

 606 def get_metadata_from_dist(dist):
 607     # type: (Union[PathMetadata, EggInfoDistribution, DistInfoDistribution]) -> Dict[S, Union[S, List[RequirementType], Dict[S, RequirementType]]]
 608     try:
 609         requires = dist.requires()
 610     except Exception:
 611         requires = []
 612     try:
 613         dep_map = dist._build_dep_map()
 614     except Exception:
 615         dep_map = {}
 616     deps = []  # type: List[PkgResourcesRequirement]
 617     extras = {}
 618     for k in dep_map.keys():
 619         if k is None:
 620             deps.extend(dep_map.get(k))
 621             continue
 622         else:
 623             extra = None
 624             _deps = dep_map.get(k)
 625             if k.startswith(":python_version"):
 626                 marker = k.replace(":", "; ")
 627             else:
 628                 if ":python_version" in k:
 629                     extra, _, marker = k.partition(":")
 630                     marker = "; {0}".format(marker)
 631                 else:
 632                     marker = ""
 633                     extra = "{0}".format(k)
 634             _deps = ensure_reqs(
 635                 tuple(["{0}{1}".format(str(req), marker) for req in _deps])
 636             )
 637             if extra:
 638                 extras[extra] = _deps
 639             else:
 640                 deps.extend(_deps)
 641     requires.extend(deps)
 642     return {
 643         "name": dist.project_name,
 644         "version": dist.version,
 645         "requires": requires,
 646         "extras": extras,
 647     }

 690 class Analyzer(ast.NodeVisitor):
 691     def __init__(self):
 692         self.name_types = []
 693         self.function_map = {}  # type: Dict[Any, Any]
 694         self.function_names = {}
 695         self.resolved_function_names = {}
 696         self.functions = []
 697         self.strings = []
 698         self.assignments = {}
 699         self.binOps = []
 700         self.binOps_map = {}
 701         self.recurse = True
 702         super(Analyzer, self).__init__()
 703 
 704     def generic_visit(self, node):
 705         if isinstance(node, ast.Call):
 706             self.functions.append(node)
 707             self.function_map.update(ast_unparse(node, initial_mapping=True))
 708         if isinstance(node, ast.Name):
 709             self.name_types.append(node)
 710         if isinstance(node, ast.Str):
 711             self.strings.append(node)
 712         if isinstance(node, ASSIGN_NODES):
 713             self.assignments.update(ast_unparse(node, initial_mapping=True))
 714         super(Analyzer, self).generic_visit(node)
 715 
 716     @contextlib.contextmanager
 717     def no_recurse(self):
 718         original_recurse_val = self.recurse
 719         try:
 720             self.recurse = False
 721             yield
 722         finally:
 723             self.recurse = original_recurse_val
 724 
 725     def visit_BinOp(self, node):
 726         node = ast_unparse(node, initial_mapping=True)
 727         self.binOps.append(node)
 728 
 729     def unmap_binops(self):
 730         for binop in self.binOps:
 731             self.binOps_map[binop] = ast_unparse(binop, analyzer=self)
 732 
 733     def match_assignment_str(self, match):
 734         matches = [k for k in self.assignments if getattr(k, "id", "") == match]
 735         if matches:
 736             return matches[-1]
 737         return None
 738 
 739     def match_assignment_name(self, match):
 740         matches = [k for k in self.assignments if getattr(k, "id", "") == match.id]
 741         if matches:
 742             return matches[-1]
 743         return None
 744 
 745     def generic_unparse(self, item):
 746         if any(isinstance(item, k) for k in AST_BINOP_MAP.keys()):
 747             return AST_BINOP_MAP[type(item)]
 748         elif any(isinstance(item, k) for k in AST_COMPARATORS.keys()):
 749             return AST_COMPARATORS[type(item)]
 750         return item
 751 
 752     def unparse(self, item):
 753         unparser = getattr(
 754             self, "unparse_{0}".format(item.__class__.__name__), self.generic_unparse
 755         )
 756         return unparser(item)
 757 
 758     def unparse_Dict(self, item):
 759         # unparsed = dict(zip(unparse(item.keys), unparse(item.values)))
 760         return dict(
 761             (self.unparse(k), self.unparse(v)) for k, v in zip(item.keys, item.values)
 762         )
 763 
 764     def unparse_List(self, item):
 765         return [self.unparse(el) for el in item.elts]
 766 
 767     def unparse_Tuple(self, item):
 768         return tuple([self.unparse(el) for el in item.elts])
 769 
 770     def unparse_Str(self, item):
 771         return item.s
 772 
 773     def unparse_Subscript(self, item):
 774         unparsed = self.unparse(item.value)
 775         if isinstance(item.slice, ast.Index):
 776             try:
 777                 unparsed = unparsed[self.unparse(item.slice.value)]
 778             except (KeyError, TypeError):
 779                 # not everything can be looked up before runtime
 780                 unparsed = item
 781         return unparsed
 782 
 783     def unparse_Num(self, item):
 784         return item.n
 785 
 786     def unparse_BinOp(self, item):
 787         if item in self.binOps_map:
 788             unparsed = self.binOps_map[item]
 789         else:
 790             right_item = self.unparse(item.right)
 791             left_item = self.unparse(item.left)
 792             op = getattr(item, "op", None)
 793             op_func = self.unparse(op) if op is not None else op
 794             try:
 795                 unparsed = op_func(left_item, right_item)
 796             except Exception:
 797                 unparsed = (left_item, op_func, right_item)
 798         return unparsed
 799 
 800     def unparse_Name(self, item):
 801         unparsed = item.id
 802         if not self.recurse:
 803             return unparsed
 804         if item in self.assignments and self.recurse:
 805             items = self.unparse(self.assignments[item])
 806             unparsed = items.get(item.id, item.id)
 807         else:
 808             assignment = self.match_assignment_name(item)
 809             if assignment is not None:
 810                 items = self.unparse(self.assignments[assignment])
 811                 unparsed = items.get(item.id, item.id)
 812         return unparsed

 814     def unparse_NameConstant(self, item):
 815         return item.value
 816 
 817     def unparse_Constant(self, item):
 818         return item.value
 819 
 820     def unparse_Ellipsis(self, item):
 821         return item.value
 822 
 823     def unparse_Attribute(self, item):
 824         attr_name = getattr(item, "value", None)
 825         attr_attr = getattr(item, "attr", None)
 826         name = None
 827         name = self.unparse(attr_name) if attr_name is not None else attr_attr
 828         if attr_name and not self.recurse:
 829             name = attr_name
 830         elif name and attr_attr:
 831             if isinstance(name, six.string_types):
 832                 unparsed = ".".join([item for item in (name, attr_attr) if item])
 833             else:
 834                 unparsed = item
 835         elif attr_attr and not name:
 836             unparsed = attr_attr
 837         else:
 838             unparsed = name if not unparsed else unparsed
 839         return unparsed

 841     def unparse_Compare(self, item):
 842         if isinstance(item.left, ast.Attribute) or isinstance(item.left, ast.Str):
 843             import importlib
 844 
 845             left = self.unparse(item.left)
 846             if "." in left:
 847                 name, _, val = left.rpartition(".")
 848                 left = getattr(importlib.import_module(name), val, left)
 849             comparators = []
 850             for comparator in item.comparators:
 851                 right = self.unparse(comparator)
 852                 if isinstance(comparator, ast.Attribute) and "." in right:
 853                     name, _, val = right.rpartition(".")
 854                     right = getattr(importlib.import_module(name), val, right)
 855                 comparators.append(right)
 856             unparsed = (left, self.unparse(item.ops), comparators)
 857         else:
 858             unparsed = item
 859         return unparsed
 860 
 861     def unparse_IfExp(self, item):
 862         ops, truth_vals = [], []
 863         if isinstance(item.test, ast.Compare):
 864             left, ops, right = self.unparse(item.test)
 865         else:
 866             result = self.unparse(item.test)
 867             if isinstance(result, dict):
 868                 k, v = result.popitem()
 869                 if not v:
 870                     truth_vals = [False]
 871         for i, op in enumerate(ops):
 872             if i == 0:
 873                 truth_vals.append(op(left, right[i]))
 874             else:
 875                 truth_vals.append(op(right[i - 1], right[i]))
 876         if all(truth_vals):
 877             unparsed = self.unparse(item.body)
 878         else:
 879             unparsed = self.unparse(item.orelse)
 880         return unparsed
 881 
 882     def unparse_Call(self, item):
 883         unparsed = {}
 884         if isinstance(item.func, (ast.Name, ast.Attribute)):
 885             func_name = self.unparse(item.func)
 886         else:
 887             try:
 888                 func_name = self.unparse(item.func)
 889             except Exception:
 890                 func_name = None
 891         if not func_name:
 892             return {}
 893         if isinstance(func_name, dict):
 894             unparsed.update(func_name)
 895             func_name = next(iter(func_name.keys()))
 896         else:
 897             unparsed[func_name] = {}
 898         for key in ("kwargs", "keywords"):
 899             val = getattr(item, key, [])
 900             if val is None:
 901                 continue
 902             for keyword in self.unparse(val):
 903                 unparsed[func_name].update(self.unparse(keyword))
 904         return unparsed
 905 
 906     def unparse_keyword(self, item):
 907         return {self.unparse(item.arg): self.unparse(item.value)}
 908 
 909     def unparse_Assign(self, item):
 910         # XXX: DO NOT UNPARSE THIS
 911         # XXX: If we unparse this it becomes impossible to map it back
 912         # XXX: To the original node in the AST so we can find the
 913         # XXX: Original reference
 914         with self.no_recurse():
 915             target = self.unparse(next(iter(item.targets)))
 916             val = self.unparse(item.value)
 917         if isinstance(target, (tuple, set, list)):
 918             unparsed = dict(zip(target, val))
 919         else:
 920             unparsed = {target: val}
 921         return unparsed
 922 
 923     def unparse_Mapping(self, item):
 924         unparsed = {}
 925         for k, v in item.items():
 926             try:
 927                 unparsed[self.unparse(k)] = self.unparse(v)
 928             except TypeError:
 929                 unparsed[k] = self.unparse(v)
 930         return unparsed
 931 
 932     def unparse_list(self, item):
 933         return type(item)([self.unparse(el) for el in item])
 934 
 935     def unparse_tuple(self, item):
 936         return self.unparse_list(item)
 937 
 938     def unparse_str(self, item):
 939         return item

 941     def parse_function_names(self, should_retry=True, function_map=None):
 942         if function_map is None:
 943             function_map = {}
 944         retries = []
 945         for k, v in function_map.items():
 946             fn_name = ""
 947             if k in self.function_names:
 948                 fn_name = self.function_names[k]
 949             elif isinstance(k, ast.Name):
 950                 fn_name = k.id
 951             elif isinstance(k, ast.Attribute):
 952                 try:
 953                     fn = ast_unparse(k, analyzer=self)
 954                 except Exception:
 955                     if should_retry:
 956                         retries.append((k, v))
 957                     continue
 958                 else:
 959                     if isinstance(fn, six.string_types):
 960                         _, _, fn_name = fn.rpartition(".")
 961             if fn_name:
 962                 self.resolved_function_names[fn_name] = ast_unparse(v, analyzer=self)
 963         return retries
 964 
 965     def parse_functions(self):
 966         retries = self.parse_function_names(function_map=self.function_map)
 967         if retries:
 968             failures = self.parse_function_names(
 969                 should_retry=False, function_map=dict(retries)
 970             )
 971         return self.resolved_function_names
 972 
 973     def parse_setup_function(self):
 974         setup = {}  # type: Dict[Any, Any]
 975         self.unmap_binops()
 976         function_names = self.parse_functions()
 977         if "setup" in function_names:
 978             setup = self.unparse(function_names["setup"])
 979         keys = list(setup.keys())
 980         if len(keys) == 1 and keys[0] is None:
 981             _, setup = setup.popitem()
 982         keys = list(setup.keys())
 983         for k in keys:
 984             # XXX: Remove unresolved functions from the setup dictionary
 985             if isinstance(setup[k], dict):
 986                 if not setup[k]:
 987                     continue
 988                 key = next(iter(setup[k].keys()))
 989                 val = setup[k][key]
 990                 if key in function_names and val is None or val == {}:
 991                     setup.pop(k)
 992         return setup

 995 def ast_unparse(item, initial_mapping=False, analyzer=None, recurse=True):  # noqa:C901
 996     # type: (Any, bool, Optional[Analyzer], bool) -> Union[List[Any], Dict[Any, Any], Tuple[Any, ...], STRING_TYPE]
 997     unparse = partial(
 998         ast_unparse, initial_mapping=initial_mapping, analyzer=analyzer, recurse=recurse
 999     )
1000     if getattr(ast, "Constant", None):
1001         constant = (ast.Constant, ast.Ellipsis)
1002     else:
1003         constant = ast.Ellipsis
1004     unparsed = item
1005     if isinstance(item, ast.Dict):
1006         unparsed = dict(zip(unparse(item.keys), unparse(item.values)))
1007     elif isinstance(item, ast.List):
1008         unparsed = [unparse(el) for el in item.elts]
1009     elif isinstance(item, ast.Tuple):
1010         unparsed = tuple([unparse(el) for el in item.elts])
1011     elif isinstance(item, ast.Str):
1012         unparsed = item.s
1013     elif isinstance(item, ast.Subscript):
1014         unparsed = unparse(item.value)
1015         if not initial_mapping:
1016             if isinstance(item.slice, ast.Index):
1017                 try:
1018                     unparsed = unparsed[unparse(item.slice.value)]
1019                 except (KeyError, TypeError):
1020                     # not everything can be looked up before runtime
1021                     unparsed = item
1022     elif any(isinstance(item, k) for k in AST_BINOP_MAP.keys()):
1023         unparsed = AST_BINOP_MAP[type(item)]
1024     elif isinstance(item, ast.Num):
1025         unparsed = item.n
1026     elif isinstance(item, ast.BinOp):
1027         if analyzer and item in analyzer.binOps_map:
1028             unparsed = analyzer.binOps_map[item]
1029         else:
1030             right_item = unparse(item.right)
1031             left_item = unparse(item.left)
1032             op = getattr(item, "op", None)
1033             op_func = unparse(op) if op is not None else op
1034             if not initial_mapping:
1035                 try:
1036                     unparsed = op_func(left_item, right_item)
1037                 except Exception:
1038                     unparsed = (left_item, op_func, right_item)
1039             else:
1040                 item.left = left_item
1041                 item.right = right_item
1042                 item.op = op_func
1043                 unparsed = item
1044     elif isinstance(item, ast.Name):
1045         if not initial_mapping:
1046             unparsed = item.id
1047             if analyzer and recurse:
1048                 if item in analyzer.assignments:
1049                     items = unparse(analyzer.assignments[item])
1050                     unparsed = items.get(item.id, item.id)
1051                 else:
1052                     assignment = analyzer.match_assignment_name(item)
1053                     if assignment is not None:
1054                         items = unparse(analyzer.assignments[assignment])
1055                         unparsed = items.get(item.id, item.id)
1056         else:
1057             unparsed = item
1058     elif six.PY3 and isinstance(item, ast.NameConstant):
1059         unparsed = item.value
1060     elif any(isinstance(item, k) for k in AST_COMPARATORS.keys()):
1061         unparsed = AST_COMPARATORS[type(item)]
1062     elif isinstance(item, constant):
1063         unparsed = item.value
1064     elif isinstance(item, ast.Compare):
1065         if isinstance(item.left, ast.Attribute) or isinstance(item.left, ast.Str):
1066             import importlib
1067 
1068             left = unparse(item.left)
1069             if "." in left:
1070                 name, _, val = left.rpartition(".")
1071                 left = getattr(importlib.import_module(name), val, left)
1072             comparators = []
1073             for comparator in item.comparators:
1074                 right = unparse(comparator)
1075                 if isinstance(comparator, ast.Attribute) and "." in right:
1076                     name, _, val = right.rpartition(".")
1077                     right = getattr(importlib.import_module(name), val, right)
1078                 comparators.append(right)
1079             unparsed = (left, unparse(item.ops), comparators)
1080     elif isinstance(item, ast.IfExp):
1081         if initial_mapping:
1082             unparsed = item
1083         else:
1084             ops, truth_vals = [], []
1085             if isinstance(item.test, ast.Compare):
1086                 left, ops, right = unparse(item.test)
1087             else:
1088                 result = ast_unparse(item.test)
1089                 if isinstance(result, dict):
1090                     k, v = result.popitem()
1091                     if not v:
1092                         truth_vals = [False]
1093             for i, op in enumerate(ops):
1094                 if i == 0:
1095                     truth_vals.append(op(left, right[i]))
1096                 else:
1097                     truth_vals.append(op(right[i - 1], right[i]))
1098             if all(truth_vals):
1099                 unparsed = unparse(item.body)
1100             else:
1101                 unparsed = unparse(item.orelse)
1102     elif isinstance(item, ast.Attribute):
1103         attr_name = getattr(item, "value", None)
1104         attr_attr = getattr(item, "attr", None)
1105         name = None
1106         if initial_mapping:
1107             unparsed = item
1108         elif attr_name and not recurse:
1109             name = attr_name
1110         else:
1111             name = unparse(attr_name) if attr_name is not None else attr_attr
1112         if name and attr_attr:
1113             if not initial_mapping and isinstance(name, six.string_types):
1114                 unparsed = ".".join([item for item in (name, attr_attr) if item])
1115             else:
1116                 unparsed = item
1117         elif attr_attr and not name and not initial_mapping:
1118             unparsed = attr_attr
1119         else:
1120             unparsed = name if not unparsed else unparsed
1121     elif isinstance(item, ast.Call):
1122         unparsed = {}
1123         if isinstance(item.func, (ast.Name, ast.Attribute)):
1124             func_name = unparse(item.func)
1125         else:
1126             try:
1127                 func_name = unparse(item.func)
1128             except Exception:
1129                 func_name = None
1130         if func_name and not isinstance(func_name, dict):
1131             unparsed[func_name] = {}
1132         if isinstance(func_name, dict):
1133             unparsed.update(func_name)
1134             func_name = next(iter(func_name.keys()))
1135         if func_name:
1136             for key in ("kwargs", "keywords"):
1137                 val = getattr(item, key, [])
1138                 if val is None:
1139                     continue
1140                 if isinstance(val, ast.Name):
1141                     unparsed[func_name] = val
1142                 else:
1143                     for keyword in unparse(val):
1144                         unparsed[func_name].update(unparse(keyword))
1145     elif isinstance(item, ast.keyword):
1146         unparsed = {unparse(item.arg): unparse(item.value)}
1147     elif isinstance(item, ASSIGN_NODES):
1148         # XXX: DO NOT UNPARSE THIS
1149         # XXX: If we unparse this it becomes impossible to map it back
1150         # XXX: To the original node in the AST so we can find the
1151         # XXX: Original reference
1152         try:
1153             targets = item.targets  # for ast.Assign
1154         except AttributeError:      # for ast.AnnAssign
1155             targets = (item.target,)
1156         if not initial_mapping:
1157             target = unparse(next(iter(targets)), recurse=False)
1158             val = unparse(item.value, recurse=False)
1159             if isinstance(target, (tuple, set, list)):
1160                 unparsed = dict(zip(target, val))
1161             else:
1162                 unparsed = {target: val}
1163         else:
1164             unparsed = {next(iter(targets)): item}
1165     elif isinstance(item, Mapping):
1166         unparsed = {}
1167         for k, v in item.items():
1168             try:
1169                 unparsed[unparse(k)] = unparse(v)
1170             except TypeError:
1171                 unparsed[k] = unparse(v)
1172     elif isinstance(item, (list, tuple)):
1173         unparsed = type(item)([unparse(el) for el in item])
1174     elif isinstance(item, six.string_types):
1175         unparsed = item
1176     return unparsed

1179 def ast_parse_attribute_from_file(path, attribute):
1180     # type: (S) -> Any
1181     analyzer = ast_parse_file(path)
1182     target_value = None
1183     for k, v in analyzer.assignments.items():
1184         name = ""
1185         if isinstance(k, ast.Name):
1186             name = k.id
1187         elif isinstance(k, ast.Attribute):
1188             fn = ast_unparse(k)
1189             if isinstance(fn, six.string_types):
1190                 _, _, name = fn.rpartition(".")
1191         if name == attribute:
1192             target_value = ast_unparse(v, analyzer=analyzer)
1193             break
1194     if isinstance(target_value, Mapping) and attribute in target_value:
1195         return target_value[attribute]
1196     return target_value

1199 def ast_parse_file(path):
1200     # type: (S) -> Analyzer
1201     try:
1202         tree = ast.parse(read_source(path))
1203     except SyntaxError:
1204         # The source may be encoded strangely, e.g. azure-storage
1205         # which has a setup.py encoded with utf-8-sig
1206         with open(path, "rb") as fh:
1207             contents = fh.read()
1208         encoding = chardet.detect(contents)["encoding"]
1209         tree = ast.parse(contents.decode(encoding))
1210     ast_analyzer = Analyzer()
1211     ast_analyzer.visit(tree)
1212     return ast_analyzer

1215 def ast_parse_setup_py(path):
1216     # type: (S) -> Dict[Any, Any]
1217     ast_analyzer = ast_parse_file(path)
1218     setup = {}  # type: Dict[Any, Any]
1219     ast_analyzer.unmap_binops()
1220     function_names = ast_analyzer.parse_functions()
1221     if "setup" in function_names:
1222         setup = ast_unparse(function_names["setup"], analyzer=ast_analyzer)
1223     keys = list(setup.keys())
1224     if len(keys) == 1 and keys[0] is None:
1225         _, setup = setup.popitem()
1226     keys = list(setup.keys())
1227     for k in keys:
1228         # XXX: Remove unresolved functions from the setup dictionary
1229         if isinstance(setup[k], dict):
1230             if not setup[k]:
1231                 continue
1232             key = next(iter(setup[k].keys()))
1233             val = setup[k][key]
1234             if key in function_names and val is None or val == {}:
1235                 setup.pop(k)
1236     return setup

1239 def run_setup(script_path, egg_base=None):
1240     # type: (str, Optional[str]) -> Distribution
1241     """Run a `setup.py` script with a target **egg_base** if provided.
1242 
1243     :param S script_path: The path to the `setup.py` script to run
1244     :param Optional[S] egg_base: The metadata directory to build in
1245     :raises FileNotFoundError: If the provided `script_path` does not exist
1246     :return: The metadata dictionary
1247     :rtype: Dict[Any, Any]
1248     """
1249 
1250     if not os.path.exists(script_path):
1251         raise FileNotFoundError(script_path)
1252     target_cwd = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(script_path))
1253     if egg_base is None:
1254         egg_base = os.path.join(target_cwd, "reqlib-metadata")
1255     with temp_path(), cd(target_cwd), _suppress_distutils_logs():
1256         # This is for you, Hynek
1257         # see https://github.com/hynek/environ_config/blob/69b1c8a/setup.py
1258         args = ["egg_info"]
1259         if egg_base:
1260             args += ["--egg-base", egg_base]
1261         script_name = os.path.basename(script_path)
1262         g = {"__file__": script_name, "__name__": "__main__"}
1263         sys.path.insert(0, target_cwd)
1264         local_dict = {}
1265         if sys.version_info < (3, 5):
1266             save_argv = sys.argv
1267         else:
1268             save_argv = sys.argv.copy()
1269         try:
1270             global _setup_distribution, _setup_stop_after
1271             _setup_stop_after = "run"
1272             sys.argv[0] = script_name
1273             sys.argv[1:] = args
1274             with open(script_name, "rb") as f:
1275                 contents = f.read()
1276                 if six.PY3:
1277                     contents.replace(br"\r\n", br"\n")
1278                 else:
1279                     contents.replace(r"\r\n", r"\n")
1280                 if sys.version_info < (3, 5):
1281                     exec(contents, g, local_dict)
1282                 else:
1283                     exec(contents, g)
1284         # We couldn't import everything needed to run setup
1285         except Exception:
1286             python = os.environ.get("PIP_PYTHON_PATH", sys.executable)
1287             out, _ = run(
1288                 [python, "setup.py"] + args,
1289                 cwd=target_cwd,
1290                 block=True,
1291                 combine_stderr=False,
1292                 return_object=False,
1293                 nospin=True,
1294             )
1295         finally:
1296             _setup_stop_after = None
1297             sys.argv = save_argv
1298             _setup_distribution = get_metadata(egg_base, metadata_type="egg")
1299         dist = _setup_distribution
1300     return dist

1454     def update_from_dict(self, metadata):
1455         name = metadata.get("name", self.name)
1456         if isinstance(name, six.string_types):
1457             self.name = self.name if self.name else name
1458         version = metadata.get("version", None)
1459         if version:
1460             try:
1461                 packaging.version.parse(version)
1462             except TypeError:
1463                 version = self.version if self.version else None
1464             else:
1465                 version = version
1466         if version:
1467             self._version = version
1468         build_requires = metadata.get("build_requires", [])
1469         if self.build_requires is None:
1470             self.build_requires = ()
1471         self.build_requires = tuple(set(self.build_requires) | set(build_requires))
1472         self._requirements = (
1473             frozenset() if self._requirements is None else self._requirements
1474         )
1475         requirements = set(self._requirements)
1476         install_requires = make_base_requirements(metadata.get("install_requires", []))
1477         requirements |= install_requires
1478         setup_requires = make_base_requirements(metadata.get("setup_requires", []))
1479         if self.setup_requires is None:
1480             self.setup_requires = ()
1481         self.setup_requires = tuple(set(self.setup_requires) | setup_requires)
1482         if self.ireq.editable:
1483             requirements |= setup_requires

1485         self.python_requires = metadata.get("python_requires", self.python_requires)
1486         extras_require = metadata.get("extras_require", {})
1487         extras_tuples = []
1488         for section in set(list(extras_require.keys())) - set(list(self.extras.keys())):
1489             extras = extras_require[section]
1490             extras_set = make_base_requirements(extras)
1491             if self.ireq and self.ireq.extras and section in self.ireq.extras:
1492                 requirements |= extras_set
1493             extras_tuples.append((section, tuple(extras_set)))
1494         if self._extras_requirements is None:
1495             self._extras_requirements = ()
1496         self._extras_requirements += tuple(extras_tuples)
1497         build_backend = metadata.get("build_backend", "setuptools.build_meta:__legacy__")
1498         if not self.build_backend:
1499             self.build_backend = build_backend
1500         self._requirements = frozenset(requirements)

1538     def run_setup(self):
1539         # type: () -> "SetupInfo"
1540         if self.setup_py is not None and self.setup_py.exists():
1541             dist = run_setup(self.setup_py.as_posix(), egg_base=self.egg_base)

1547                         return self.populate_metadata(metadata)

1549                 if isinstance(dist, Mapping):
1550                     self.populate_metadata(dist)

1553                 if name:

1564                     dist.get_requires()

1567                     update_dict["setup_requires"] = make_base_requirements(
1568                         dist.setup_requires
1569                     )

1571                 if version:

1712     def populate_metadata(self, metadata):
1713         # type: (Dict[Any, Any]) -> "SetupInfo"
1714         """Populates the metadata dictionary from the supplied metadata.
1715 
1716         :return: The current instance.
1717         :rtype: `SetupInfo`
1718         """
1719 
1720         _metadata = ()
1721         for k, v in metadata.items():
1722             if k == "extras" and isinstance(v, dict):
1723                 extras = ()
1724                 for extra, reqs in v.items():
1725                     extras += ((extra, tuple(reqs)),)
1726                 _metadata += extras
1727             elif isinstance(v, (list, tuple)):
1728                 _metadata += (k, tuple(v))
1729             else:
1730                 _metadata += (k, v)
1731         self.metadata = _metadata
1732         cleaned = metadata.copy()
1733         cleaned.update({"install_requires": metadata.get("requires", [])})
1734         if cleaned:
1735             self.update_from_dict(cleaned.copy())
1736         else:
1737             self.update_from_dict(metadata)
1738         return self

1764     def get_initial_info(self):

1766         parse_setupcfg = False
1767         parse_setuppy = False
1768         if self.setup_cfg and self.setup_cfg.exists():
1769             parse_setupcfg = True
1770         if self.setup_py and self.setup_py.exists():
1771             parse_setuppy = True
1772         if parse_setuppy or parse_setupcfg:
1773             with cd(self.base_dir):
1774                 if parse_setuppy:
1775                     self.update_from_dict(self.parse_setup_py())
1776                 if parse_setupcfg:
1777                     self.update_from_dict(self.parse_setup_cfg())
1778             if self.name is not None and any(
1779                 [
1780                     self.requires,
1781                     self.setup_requires,
1782                     self._extras_requirements,
1783                     self.build_backend,
1784                 ]
1785             ):
1786                 return self.as_dict()
1787         return self.get_info()
1788 
1789     def get_info(self):
1790         # type: () -> Dict[S, Any]
1791         with cd(self.base_dir):
1792             self.run_pyproject()
1793             self.build()
1794 
1795         if self.setup_py and self.setup_py.exists() and self.metadata is None:
1796             if not self.requires or not self.name:
1797                 try:
1798                     with cd(self.base_dir):
1799                         self.run_setup()
1800                 except Exception:
1801                     with cd(self.base_dir):
1802                         metadata = self.get_egg_metadata()
1803                         if metadata:
1804                             self.populate_metadata(metadata)
1805                 if self.metadata is None or not self.name:
1806                     with cd(self.base_dir):
1807                         metadata = self.get_egg_metadata()
1808                         if metadata:
1809                             self.populate_metadata(metadata)
1810 
1811         return self.as_dict()

1815         prop_dict = {
1816             "name": self.name,

1818             "base_dir": self.base_dir,
1819             "ireq": self.ireq,
1820             "build_backend": self.build_backend,
1821             "build_requires": self.build_requires,
1822             "requires": self.requires if self._requirements else None,

1829             "pyproject": self.pyproject,

1840     @classmethod
1841     @lru_cache()
1842     def from_ireq(cls, ireq, subdir=None, finder=None, session=None):
1843         # type: (InstallRequirement, Optional[AnyStr], Optional[PackageFinder], Optional[requests.Session]) -> Optional[SetupInfo]
1844         import pip_shims.shims
1845 
1846         if not ireq.link:
1847             return None
1848         if ireq.link.is_wheel:
1849             return None
1850         stack = ExitStack()
1851         if not session:
1852             cmd = pip_shims.shims.InstallCommand()
1853             options, _ = cmd.parser.parse_args([])
1854             session = cmd._build_session(options)
1855             finder = cmd._build_package_finder(options, session)
1856         tempdir_manager = stack.enter_context(pip_shims.shims.global_tempdir_manager())
1857         vcs, uri = split_vcs_method_from_uri(unquote(ireq.link.url_without_fragment))
1858         parsed = urlparse(uri)
1859         if "file" in parsed.scheme:
1860             url_path = parsed.path
1861             if "@" in url_path:
1862                 url_path, _, _ = url_path.rpartition("@")
1863             parsed = parsed._replace(path=url_path)
1864             uri = urlunparse(parsed)
1865         path = None
1866         is_file = False
1867         if ireq.link.scheme == "file" or uri.startswith("file://"):
1868             is_file = True
1869             if "file:/" in uri and "file:///" not in uri:
1870                 uri = uri.replace("file:/", "file:///")
1871             path = pip_shims.shims.url_to_path(uri)
1872         kwargs = _prepare_wheel_building_kwargs(ireq)
1873         is_artifact_or_vcs = getattr(
1874             ireq.link, "is_vcs", getattr(ireq.link, "is_artifact", False)
1875         )
1876         is_vcs = True if vcs else is_artifact_or_vcs
1877         if is_file and not is_vcs and path is not None and os.path.isdir(path):
1878             target = os.path.join(kwargs["src_dir"], os.path.basename(path))
1879             shutil.copytree(path, target, symlinks=True)
1880             ireq.source_dir = target
1881         if not (ireq.editable and is_file and is_vcs):
1882             if ireq.is_wheel:
1883                 only_download = True
1884                 download_dir = kwargs["wheel_download_dir"]
1885             else:
1886                 only_download = False
1887                 download_dir = kwargs["download_dir"]
1888         elif path is not None and os.path.isdir(path):
1889             raise RequirementError(
1890                 "The file URL points to a directory not installable: {}".format(ireq.link)
1891             )
1892         # this ensures the build dir is treated as the temporary build location
1893         # and the source dir is treated as permanent / not deleted by pip
1894         build_location_func = getattr(ireq, "build_location", None)
1895         if build_location_func is None:
1896             build_location_func = getattr(ireq, "ensure_build_location", None)
1897         if not ireq.source_dir:
1898             build_kwargs = {"build_dir": kwargs["build_dir"], "autodelete": False}
1899             call_function_with_correct_args(build_location_func, **build_kwargs)
1900             ireq.ensure_has_source_dir(kwargs["src_dir"])
1901             src_dir = ireq.source_dir
1902             pip_shims.shims.shim_unpack(
1903                 download_dir=download_dir,
1904                 ireq=ireq,
1905                 only_download=only_download,
1906                 session=session,
1907                 hashes=ireq.hashes(False),
1908             )
1909         created = cls.create(
1910             ireq.source_dir, subdirectory=subdir, ireq=ireq, kwargs=kwargs, stack=stack
1911         )
1912         return created
1913 
1914     @classmethod
1915     def create(
1916         cls,
1917         base_dir,  # type: str
1918         subdirectory=None,  # type: Optional[str]
1919         ireq=None,  # type: Optional[InstallRequirement]
1920         kwargs=None,  # type: Optional[Dict[str, str]]
1921         stack=None,  # type: Optional[ExitStack]
1922     ):
1923         # type: (...) -> Optional[SetupInfo]
1924         if not base_dir or base_dir is None:
1925             return None
1926 
1927         creation_kwargs = {"extra_kwargs": kwargs}
1928         if not isinstance(base_dir, Path):
1929             base_dir = Path(base_dir)
1930         creation_kwargs["base_dir"] = base_dir.as_posix()
1931         pyproject = base_dir.joinpath("pyproject.toml")
1932 
1933         if subdirectory is not None:
1934             base_dir = base_dir.joinpath(subdirectory)
1935         setup_py = base_dir.joinpath("setup.py")
1936         setup_cfg = base_dir.joinpath("setup.cfg")
1937         creation_kwargs["pyproject"] = pyproject
1938         creation_kwargs["setup_py"] = setup_py
1939         creation_kwargs["setup_cfg"] = setup_cfg
1940         if stack is None:
1941             stack = ExitStack()
1942         creation_kwargs["stack"] = stack
1943         if ireq:
1944             creation_kwargs["ireq"] = ireq
1945         created = cls(**creation_kwargs)
1946         created.get_initial_info()
1947         return created
